    {
      "id": "3115dbab_125ea28e",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/impl/NetworkCmProxyCmHandlerQueryServiceImpl.java",
      "patchset_number": 11,
      "line": 159,
      "message": "I think we agreed originally (during analysis with team) to always execute a single getCmHandle with a full path (instead of cpsPath query). using get all will not scale well and result in a slow return even if the result is only a few cm-handles\n\nwe need to time, given an environment with 10,000 cmHandles\n\nA) getAll CMhandles methods\nB) 10,000 individual het cm handle calls\n\nIf B is not much slower than A we should always use the individual approach (preferred)\nif B is much slower we need to find/calculate a threshold to decide which approach to take in the code e.g. 1,000 nodes",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2022-06-28 15:20:10.000000000",
